// Rider–Waite–Smith tarot, all 78 cards. Public domain: the deck was
// first published in 1909; the divinatory meanings below are
// condensed from A. E. Waite's "The Pictorial Key to the Tarot"
// (1911), also public domain.
//
// Each entry branches on {$facing}, which the Randomness deck engine
// sets per draw (reversal chance is a per-deck setting; this bundle
// ships deck.json with 50%). Add card images to this folder — one
// per card, named to match the keys (e.g. "the-tower.png") — and
// draws will show the art too.
Title: Tarot (Rider–Waite–Smith)
Table: Tarot
Type: Dictionary
The Fool: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Hesitation, recklessness exposed, a false start.[else]A leap of faith, new beginnings, innocence on the road.[end]
The Magician: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Trickery, misused skill, will bent to deception.[else]Skill, willpower, resources at hand made real.[end]
The High Priestess: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Secrets withheld, surface knowledge, intuition ignored.[else]Hidden knowledge, intuition, the unrevealed future.[end]
The Empress: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Neglect, creative block, smothering care.[else]Fruitfulness, abundance, nurture and growth.[end]
The Emperor: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Tyranny, rigidity, authority undermined.[else]Authority, structure, protection through order.[end]
The Hierophant: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Unconventional paths, dogma rejected, bad counsel.[else]Tradition, guidance, alliance with institutions.[end]
The Lovers: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Discord, temptation chosen poorly, a union strained.[else]Love, harmony, a choice of the heart.[end]
The Chariot: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Loss of control, scattered forces, a stalled campaign.[else]Triumph through will, opposing forces mastered.[end]
Strength: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Self-doubt, weakness, power abused or untamed.[else]Courage, fortitude, the beast gentled by patience.[end]
The Hermit: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Isolation curdled, counsel refused, a lamp hidden.[else]Solitude, guidance sought within, the lantern raised.[end]
Wheel of Fortune: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Ill luck, resistance to change, the turn against you.[else]Destiny turns, fortune, an unexpected change.[end]
Justice: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Injustice, bias, an unbalanced account.[else]Equity, truth, the scales set right.[end]
The Hanged Man: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Useless sacrifice, delay for nothing, martyrdom.[else]Surrender, a new view from suspension, wisdom in waiting.[end]
Death: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Stagnation, change resisted, a lingering end.[else]An ending that clears the way, transformation.[end]
Temperance: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Excess, discord of elements, impatience.[else]Moderation, blending of opposites, patient economy.[end]
The Devil: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Chains loosened, release, the spell broken.[else]Bondage, temptation, the material grip.[end]
The Tower: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Disaster narrowly averted, a needed collapse delayed.[else]Sudden upheaval, the proud structure struck down.[end]
The Star: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Hope dimmed, arrogance, a promise unfulfilled.[else]Hope, bright promise, waters poured out freely.[end]
The Moon: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Deception fading, fears faced, the fog lifting.[else]Illusion, hidden enemies, the uncertain path by night.[end]
The Sun: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Clouded joy, delayed success, vanity.[else]Joy, success, plain truth in full light.[end]
Judgement: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Self-doubt, a call refused, weak resolve.[else]Awakening, the call answered, renewal.[end]
The World: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Incompletion, a journey stalled short of its end.[else]Completion, the journey crowned, the circle closed.[end]
Ace of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]False starts, a spark smothered.[else]Creation, an enterprise begun, the spark.[end]
Two of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Fear of the unknown, plans abandoned.[else]Dominion surveyed, bold plans, the world in hand.[end]
Three of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Delays at sea, effort scattered.[else]Established strength, ships sent out, trade and foresight.[end]
Four of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Celebration postponed, insecurity at home.[else]Harvest home, celebration, peace after labour.[end]
Five of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Quarrels ended or driven underground.[else]Mock battle, competition, the strife of youth.[end]
Six of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Victory delayed, fear of a rival, pride before a fall.[else]Victory, the laurelled rider, good news carried home.[end]
Seven of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Overwhelmed, ground yielded, anxiety.[else]Valour on the high ground, holding off many.[end]
Eight of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Arrows of jealousy, quarrels, delay.[else]Swiftness, messages in flight, matters rushing to a close.[end]
Nine of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Obstacles, adversity met unprepared.[else]Strength in reserve, the wounded sentinel still standing.[end]
Ten of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]The burden dropped or shifted unfairly.[else]Oppression, a burden carried to the very door.[end]
Page of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Bad tidings, indecision, instability.[else]A faithful messenger, enthusiasm, a stranger with news.[end]
Knight of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Discord, a journey frustrated, rupture.[else]Departure, a hasty journey, adventurous energy.[end]
Queen of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Jealousy, opposition, economy turned strict.[else]Warm command, honest fire, a friend to the questioner.[end]
King of Wands: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Severity turned harsh, intolerance.[else]Honest counsel, a countryman, conscience and rule.[end]
Ace of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]A heart unmoved, joy spilt, false love.[else]The heart's fountain, joy, abundance of feeling.[end]
Two of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]A bond strained, false friendship.[else]Partnership, love pledged, concord of two.[end]
Three of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Excess of pleasure, a celebration soured.[else]Plenty, merriment, the happy issue of a matter.[end]
Four of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]New relations, novelty accepted at last.[else]Weariness with what is offered, discontent amid comfort.[end]
Five of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Return of hope, an old tie renewed.[else]Loss, three spilt and two remaining, regret over the shoulder.[end]
Six of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Living in the past, a gift refused, renewal deferred.[else]Memory, childhood kindness, a gift from the past.[end]
Seven of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Resolve, a choice finally made.[else]Castles in the clouds, many visions, imagination unanchored.[end]
Eight of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]The feast returned to, joy resumed.[else]Walking away from what was built, the quest elsewhere.[end]
Nine of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Smugness punctured, imperfect satisfaction.[else]Contentment, the wish fulfilled, well-being.[end]
Ten of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Domestic discord, false happiness.[else]Home at peace, the rainbow of cups, lasting contentment.[end]
Page of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Distraction, a shallow offer, seduction.[else]A gentle messenger, news of feeling, reflection offered.[end]
Knight of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Fraud, a proposal with a false bottom.[else]An arrival, an invitation, advances of the heart.[end]
Queen of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]A heart not to be trusted, virtue distorted.[else]Loving intelligence, the visionary queen, devoted service.[end]
King of Cups: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]A double-dealing man, scandal, loss.[else]A fair and considerate man, calm authority in feeling.[end]
Ace of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Force misused, conquest that ruins.[else]The point of truth, conquest, great force for good or ill.[end]
Two of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Duplicity, the blindfold slipping, false balance.[else]Stalemate, a guarded truce, eyes closed to the sea.[end]
Three of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Confusion of grief, loss made worse by denial.[else]Heartbreak, division, the pierced heart in rain.[end]
Four of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Enforced rest ends, cautious return to the field.[else]Rest, retreat, the knight at vigil.[end]
Five of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Loss all the same, an empty victory mourned.[else]Defeat with dishonour, swords gathered by the smirking victor.[end]
Six of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]No way out yet, a crossing postponed.[else]Passage to calmer water, a journey away from trouble.[end]
Seven of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Good counsel arrives, stolen goods returned.[else]Stealth, a plan half-carried, swords borne away from camp.[end]
Eight of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Bonds loosened, the first step out of the fence.[else]Restriction, bound and hedged by blades, crisis of doubt.[end]
Nine of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]The nightmare examined by daylight, shame eased.[else]Sleepless grief, the weight of dread at midnight.[end]
Ten of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Survival, the worst passed, slow recovery.[else]Ruin, the lowest point, pain played to its end.[end]
Page of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Spying discovered, unpreparedness.[else]Vigilance, a quick and wary scout, examination.[end]
Knight of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Ruin by recklessness, a charge into nothing.[else]Headlong skill, the gale-driven charge, brave war.[end]
Queen of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Malice sharpened by grief, narrowness.[else]Clear-eyed widow, keen judgement, truth without ornament.[end]
King of Swords: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Cruelty of the bench, a ruling perverted.[else]Judgement enthroned, command, the power of life and death.[end]
Ace of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Gold that corrupts, prosperity without comfort.[else]Perfect contentment, gold in the garden, a prosperous start.[end]
Two of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Juggling failed, letters of bad news.[else]Balance amid change, gaiety juggling fortune's tides.[end]
Three of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Mediocrity in work, pettiness.[else]Skilled work honoured, the mason in the cathedral, mastery.[end]
Four of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Delay, opposition, the grip forced open.[else]Holding fast to what is owned, the miser's crown.[end]
Five of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]A door found at last, charity received.[else]Want and hardship, two figures past the lighted window.[end]
Six of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Debt called in, charity with strings, envy.[else]Gifts justly weighed, generosity, what is owed made good.[end]
Seven of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Anxiety over money, labour wasted.[else]Pause over the harvest, appraisal, growth watched.[end]
Eight of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Skill turned to cunning, vain ambition.[else]Apprenticeship, careful craft repeated, work becoming skill.[end]
Nine of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Loss of home or friendship, a plan undone.[else]Accomplished solitude, the garden enjoyed, material grace.[end]
Ten of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Family misfortune, an inheritance disputed.[else]Inheritance, the household established, riches across generations.[end]
Page of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Dissipation, news of loss, unfocused study.[else]A diligent student, application, news of money.[end]
Knight of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Idleness, a machine stopped, discouragement.[else]Patient service, the laden knight, responsibility carried.[end]
Queen of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Suspicion, duties neglected, fear of failure.[else]Opulent care, greatness of soul, security given freely.[end]
King of Pentacles: [when]{$facing}=reversed[do]Corruption of wealth, a dangerous man of business.[else]Realised success, a reliable master of valour and trade.[end]
